  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install eudev by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --sbindir=/sbin \
            --sysconfdir=/etc \
            --disable-static \
            --enable-split-usr \
            --enable-libkmod \
            --enable-rule-generator \
            --with-rootlibdir=/lib \
            --with-rootprefix= \
            --with-firmware-path=/lib/firmware &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <option>--disable-gudev</option>: Use this switch if you want to disable
        Gobject libudev support.
      </para>

      <para>
        <option>--disable-keymap</option>: Use this switch if you want to
        disable keymap fixup support.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

